# Infrastructure-Creator Workflow

This is a PHP accelerator **generator**, not a ready-to-use accelerator. It scans a target PHP project by path, researches its real dependencies/integrations, asks the few questions evidence cannot answer, and generates a bespoke accelerator (`AGENTS.md`, skills, agents, commands, hooks, `memory-bank/`) directly into that target project's own root, for only the AI tool(s) the target team selects.

## Command -> Agent -> Skill

- **Commands** (`.cursor/commands/*.md`) are `/slash` entry points; the user-facing ones are `infra-scan`, `infra-generate`, and `infra-build`. Pass the target project path as `$ARGUMENTS`.
- **Agents** (`.cursor/agents/*.md`) each run one skill in an isolated context, then stop - except `infra-scan`, `infra-generate`, and `infra-build`, the sanctioned orchestrators (see `AGENTS.md`'s Orchestration Exception).
- **Skills** (`.cursor/skills/<name>/SKILL.md`) contain the actual workflow.

Execute only the selected skill, then stop (unless it is one of the three orchestrators). Always end with a Context Summary and Next Steps.

## Two-Phase Flow

```text
/infra-scan <target-path>
  -> stack-scanner / architecture-scanner / integration-scanner /
     infra-ops-scanner / security-compliance-scanner / conventions-scanner (parallel)
  -> stack-researcher -> clarifying-interview -> profile-synthesizer

  <-- HUMAN REVIEW CHECKPOINT: read tasks/TASK-{N}/infra-scan-project-profile.md -->

/infra-generate <target-path>
  -> policy-forge / skill-forge / hook-forge / memory-seed (parallel)
  -> agent-forge -> command-forge -> skill-flow-composer -> bootstrap-verifier
```

## Workspace Boundary

Infrastructure-Creator stays outside the project it scans/generates for, and every command requires an explicit target-path argument. Never point a command at this folder's own tree. Phase 1 is read-only on the target; Phase 2 is the only writer.
